{"word":"εὐεπής","slug":"εὐεπής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐεπής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-επής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔπος'><el>ἔπος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>well-speaking, eloquent, melodious</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>making eloquent</i>, of Helicon, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>well-spoken, acceptable</i>, <el>λόγος</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}